# Vercel Web Analytics Installation

Successfully installed and configured Vercel Web Analytics for the Next.js project.

## Changes Made

### 1. Installed Package
- Added `@vercel/analytics` version 2.0.1 to dependencies
- Updated `package.json` and `package-lock.json`

### 2. Modified Files
- **frontend/src/app/layout.tsx**
  - Added import: `import { Analytics } from "@vercel/analytics/next"`
  - Added `<Analytics />` component inside the `<body>` tag, after the `<Providers>` component
  - This follows the official Vercel documentation for Next.js App Router

### 3. Implementation Details
- Fetched latest installation instructions from https://vercel.com/docs/analytics/quickstart
- Used framework-specific integration for Next.js App Router
- Preserved existing code structure and formatting
- Placed Analytics component at the end of the body tag as recommended

### 4. Testing & Verification
✓ Build completed successfully (`npm run build`)
✓ Linter passed with no new errors (`npm run lint`)
✓ All lock files updated appropriately

## Next Steps
To enable analytics data collection:
1. Deploy the project to Vercel
2. Enable Web Analytics in the Vercel dashboard under the Analytics section
3. Analytics will start collecting data automatically once enabled

## Notes
- The `<Analytics />` component is a lightweight script that tracks page views
- It respects user privacy and is GDPR compliant
- No additional configuration is required in the code
